我们不能再陪你疯了

156
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:57,300
Penny's taking you to
the DMV. I'm going to bed.
Penny会带你去车管局 我去睡觉

157
00:09:57,310 --> 00:09:58,420
Why Penny?
为什么是Penny?

158
00:09:58,440 --> 00:10:01,540
Because rock breaks
scissors. Good night.
因为石头赢了剪刀 晚安

159
00:10:02,300 --> 00:10:04,140
All right, come on, Sheldon.
行了 走吧 Sheldon

160
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:06,420
Hold on. I have one condition.
等等 我有个条件

161
00:10:06,430 --> 00:10:07,250
What?
啥啊?

162
00:10:07,260 --> 00:10:09,670
We have to stop at Pottery Barn.
我们要在陶器坊那停一停

163
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:11,480
Okay.
行

164
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:13,900
And Radio Shack.
还有Radio Shack零售店

165
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:16,060
Fine.
好吧

166
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:18,830
- And the comic book store.
- All right!
- 漫画书店
- 知道了

167
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:22,010
Ooh, I want to go to
the comic book store.
我也要去漫画书店

168
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:43,280
I like comic books.
我喜欢漫画书

169
00:10:46,970 --> 00:10:49,940
I just don't see why I
need a driver's license.
搞不懂我考驾照干啥

170
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:53,500
Albert Einstein never
had a driver's license.
爱因斯坦都没考过的说

171
00:10:53,530 --> 00:10:58,350
Yeah, but Albert Einstein didn't make
me wet myself at 40 miles an hour.
是啊 但爱因斯坦没让我在
40英里时速下尿裤子

172
00:10:58,770 --> 00:11:02,570
Yeah, and I never wanted to
kick Albert Einstein in the nuts.
我从没想过踢爱因斯坦老二

173
00:11:05,740 --> 00:11:09,650
You know, I gotta ask, why didn't you just
get a license at 16 like everybody else?
我想问问 你干嘛不像其他人一样
16岁时就考到驾照呢?

174
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:13,070
I was otherwise engaged.
我在忙其他事情

175
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:14,610
Doing what?
忙什么?

176
00:11:14,630 --> 00:11:18,180
Examining perturbative amplitudes
in N=4 supersymmetric theories
检测N=4超对称理论的扰动振幅

177
00:11:18,190 --> 00:11:22,590
leading to a re-examination of the ultraviolet
properties of multi-loop N=8 supergravity
从而开展了利用现代扭量理论
对多线圈N=8超引力

178
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:25,370
using modern twistor theory.
紫外线特质的复查

179
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:31,460
Well, how 'bout when you were 17?
那你17岁的时候呢?

180
00:11:32,330 --> 00:11:34,430
Take this to the testing
area, put your name at the top,
拿着去测试区 表格顶端写好名字

181
00:11:34,450 --> 00:11:38,030
sign the bottom, answer the
questions, bring it back. Next.
在最底下签名 答完问题拿回来 下一个

182
00:11:43,740 --> 00:11:45,720
Application?
你的申请表呢?

183
00:11:45,750 --> 00:11:48,910
I'm actually more of a theorist.
事实上我不仅仅是一个理论家

184
00:11:50,260 --> 00:11:54,040
The application in your
hand. Give it to her.
你手里的申请表 给她

185
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,820
Take this to the testing
area, put your name at the top,
拿着去测试区 表格顶端写好名字

186
00:11:59,850 --> 00:12:02,700
sign the bottom, answer the
questions, bring it back. Next!
在最底下签名 答完问题再拿回来 下一个

187
00:12:02,710 --> 00:12:07,020
Excuse me, but I have some
concerns about these questions.
对不起 关于这些问题 我有些疑问

188
00:12:07,570 --> 00:12:09,640
Look at that sign up there.
看看那里的告示

189
00:12:09,670 --> 00:12:10,590
Yes?
嗯?

190
00:12:10,610 --> 00:12:13,320
Does it say "I give a damn"?
有没有写"我乐意搭理"呢?

191
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,010
No.
没有

192
00:12:16,020 --> 00:12:18,330
That's because I don't.
那是因为我不乐意呗

193
00:12:18,340 --> 00:12:21,310
Just look. See, this first
question makes no sense.
看一下啦 第一个问题讲不通啊

194
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:25,120
"How many car lengths should you
leave in front of you when driving?"
"开车时 你需距前车多少车长"

195
00:12:25,130 --> 00:12:27,500
There's no possible way to answer that.
不可能有答案

196
00:12:27,530 --> 00:12:31,330
A "car length" is not a
standardized unit of measure.
"车长"根本不是标准度量单位

197
00:12:31,830 --> 00:12:34,220
Look at the sign.
看告示

198
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:35,990
Sheldon, it's "C." Just put down "C."
Sheldon 是C啦 选C就好了

199
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,330
I don't need your help, Penny.
Penny 我不要你帮忙

200
00:12:37,350 --> 00:12:40,040
Listen to that little
girl, honey. Put "C." Next!
亲爱的 听那小姑娘的 选C 下一个

201
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:42,520
No, wait! No, hang on.
Look at this next question.
不 等下! 等等 看下一个问题

202
00:12:42,530 --> 00:12:46,300
Sheldon, why are you
arguing with the DMV?
Sheldon 你干嘛要和车管局的争论呢?

203
00:12:46,690 --> 00:12:49,980
How else are they going to learn?
我不吵他们咋学习进步啊?

204
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:55,140
Look... question two: When
are roadways most slippery?
看... 问题二: 什么时候路道最滑?

205
00:12:55,150 --> 00:12:57,690
Now, okay, there are three
answers, none of which are correct.
瞧 三个答案 全是错的

206
00:12:57,730 --> 00:13:02,660
The correct answer is "when covered by "a film of liquid
sufficient to reduce the coefficient of static friction"
正解是 当覆盖一层
足够减少摩擦系数的液体

207
00:13:02,670 --> 00:13:04,760
"between the tire and the
road to essentially zero,
在轮胎和路之间达到零始态

208
00:13:04,780 --> 00:13:08,720
but not so deep as to introduce
a new source of friction."
而这液态膜又不至于成为新的摩擦源

209
00:13:12,540 --> 00:13:15,420
Here's your learner's permit. Go away.
你的驾驶学习许可 快走

210
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:19,640
But I'm not done. I have many additional
concerns about these questions.
还没说完呢 关于这些问题我还有很多疑问

211
00:13:19,650 --> 00:13:21,000
Don't make me climb over this counter.
别逼我爬出柜台扁你

212
00:13:21,020 --> 00:13:23,560
Come on. Let's go.
行了 走吧

213
00:13:24,910 --> 00:13:26,640
Next!
下一个!

214
00:13:26,650 --> 00:13:28,700
Aced it.
搞定

215
00:13:31,210 --> 00:13:34,810
Okay, that's it. Let's boot it up.
好 成了 启动吧

216
00:13:34,820 --> 00:13:36,990
Booting.
启动

217
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,880
This is a
state-of-the-art simulator.
这是最先进的模拟器

218
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:41,800
I adapted it from something a
friend of mine designed for the army.
我照一朋友给军方设计改装的

219
00:13:41,810 --> 00:13:46,540
Is that why I appear to be in downtown Fallujah
behind the wheel of an up-armored Humvee?
所以我在费卢杰市区
跟在一辆全副武装的悍马后面?

220
00:13:47,030 --> 00:13:49,760
I haven't configured it yet.
还没有完全改成民用程序

221
00:13:49,770 --> 00:13:54,870
Let's see... Bradley tank...
transport truck... Batmobile...
我看看 布莱德利坦克
运输卡车  蝙蝠侠车

222
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:56,960
No.
别

223
00:13:57,260 --> 00:14:02,090
Here we go. Red 2006 Ford Taurus
on the streets of Pasadena.
好了 帕萨迪纳市街道
2006款红色福特金牛星

224
00:14:03,830 --> 00:14:04,560
What?
想说啥?

225
00:14:04,580 --> 00:14:08,630
Statistically, red cars are stopped by
police far more often than any other color.
统计显示 红车远比其他车被警察扣的多

226
00:14:08,650 --> 00:14:12,000
I don't want any hassles with the fuzz.
我可不想和警察争论

227
00:14:12,010 --> 00:14:14,470
Fine, what color do you want?
行了 你想要啥色的?

228
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:18,520
You know the pale blue of
Luke Skywalker's lightsaber?
知道天行者路克光剑的灰蓝色不?

229
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:23,430
Before it was digitally remastered?
数码制作之前的那种?

230
00:14:24,380 --> 00:14:27,640
Black, it is.
黑色 选定

231
00:14:27,650 --> 00:14:31,900
Okay, now, what you want to do first is
turn on the ignition and shift into drive.
好了 首先你要点火然后挂挡

232
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:35,210
I haven't fastened my seat belt yet.
我还没有系上安全带呢

233
00:14:36,430 --> 00:14:39,660
Okay, fasten your seat belt.
好啦 系上吧

234
00:14:45,260 --> 00:14:47,090
****
系好了

235
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:49,660
Now, are there air bags?
有安全气囊吗?

236
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:50,970
You don't need air bags.
用不着的

237
00:14:50,990 --> 00:14:52,830
What if a simulated van rear-ends me?
万一模拟货车追尾了呢?

238
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:55,560
I'll hit you in the face with a pillow.
我会用枕头打你脸的

239
00:15:04,460 --> 00:15:06,850
Okay, now shift into drive.
好 现在换到驾驶档

240
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:10,210
Pull out slowly into traffic.
慢慢驶上路

241
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:14,600
Watch out, watch, watch
out for the pedestrians!
小心 小心路人!

242
00:15:14,630 --> 00:15:19,020
Oh, God. Wait-- slow--
Hit the brakes! The brakes!
天 等等 慢点 刹车!刹车!

243
00:15:30,380 --> 00:15:32,620
Thank you.
谢了

244
00:15:35,280 --> 00:15:38,010
Sorry. Excuse me.
对不起 抱歉

245
00:15:39,530 --> 00:15:41,780
My bad.
我的错

246
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:46,190
Student driver.
新手上路

247
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:51,420
How did you manage to get on the
second floor of the Glendale Galleria?
你怎么上的格兰岱尔商场二楼的?

248
00:15:51,610 --> 00:15:54,300
I don't know. I was on
the Pasadena freeway.
不知道 我本来在帕萨迪纳高速路

249
00:15:54,310 --> 00:15:58,970
I missed my exit, flew off the
overpass, and one thing led to another.
我错过出口 飞过天桥 接二连三的...

250
00:16:01,070 --> 00:16:03,560
Maybe you want to give it a
rest and try again tomorrow.
也许你可以休息下 明天再练

251
00:16:03,580 --> 00:16:06,750
No. I quit.
不 老子不干了

252
00:16:13,790 --> 00:16:16,470
Aw, the pet store.
呀 宠物店

253
00:16:17,930 --> 00:16:22,140
Remind me to compliment Wolowitz on
the software. It's amazingly detailed.
提醒我称赞Wolowitz的软件
细节太逼真了

254
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:25,760
So wait, you're just gonna give up?
那 你准备放弃了?

255
00:16:25,770 --> 00:16:29,460
No, I'm not giving up. I never give up.
不 我才不放弃 我从不放弃

256
00:16:30,060 --> 00:16:32,380
So, what is it you're doing?
那你这是干啥呢?

257
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:36,260
I'm... transcending the situation.
我正在... 度过难关呐

258
00:16:39,830 --> 00:16:44,100
I'm clearly too evolved for driving.
显然驾驶对我来说太低级了

259
00:16:46,670 --> 00:16:48,230
What does that mean?
啥意思呢?

260
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:53,000
Leonard, have you ever wondered why
my little toes and lateral incisors
Leonard 你纳闷过为啥
我的小脚趾和侧门牙

261
00:16:53,010 --> 00:16:57,630
are significantly smaller than
the average for someone of my size?
要比和我一号的人小很多吗?

262
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:02,510
I wonder a lot of things about
you, Sheldon. But not-not that.
你有太多值得纳闷的 Sheldon
但这事没有过

263
00:17:03,220 --> 00:17:08,390
Well, those are indicators that I'm farther along
the evolutionary scale than the average human.
那显示我比普通人进化得多

264
00:17:08,410 --> 00:17:09,860
- No kidding.
- Well, no, no.
- 别搞笑了
- 别 听我说

265
00:17:09,870 --> 00:17:14,550
I'm not gonna go so far as to say that I
represent a distinct new stage in humankind--
我也不好说我处于
人类发展的一个崭新阶段

266
00:17:14,570 --> 00:17:17,840
you know, a homo novus, if you will.
你要是愿意的话 叫新新人类

267
00:17:18,530 --> 00:17:21,240
No, that's for
anthropologists to decide.
不 那要人类学家来认定的

268
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:26,270
But I am convinced that the reason I
cannot master the plebeian task of driving
但是我确信我不能精通
普通人驾驶技术的原因

269
00:17:26,320 --> 00:17:28,500
is because I'm not meant to.
是因为我注定不是干这个的

270
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:30,680
Yes, you are. You're meant
to learn how to drive.
不 你就是 你就是该学习驾驶的

271
00:17:30,690 --> 00:17:33,720
- Please learn how to drive!
- No, no.
- 求你学学开车吧!
- 不 不

272
00:17:33,730 --> 00:17:37,460
Leonard, I'm meant for greater things, like
unraveling the mysteries of the universe,
Leonard 我注定要做更伟大的事
比如解答宇宙的奥秘

273
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:42,780
not determining when it's safe to pass
a stopped school bus on a country road.
而不是搞清楚什么时候超过
一个停在乡村路上的校车是安全的

274
00:17:44,260 --> 00:17:47,130
- It's never safe.
- Yeah, well, I know that now.
- 啥时候都不安全
- 好极了 我现在知道了

275
00:17:48,940 --> 00:17:52,060
Fine. Assuming that
everything you say is true,
好 假定你说的都是真的

276
00:17:52,070 --> 00:17:57,010
how does the biologically superior
homo novus get to work tomorrow morning?
我们生物角度极其优越的新新人类
明天怎么去上班呢?

277
00:17:57,400 --> 00:18:00,400
Homo novus doesn't know.
新新人类不知道

278
00:18:00,830 --> 00:18:02,900
Well, hang in there.
那 耐心等吧

279
00:18:02,930 --> 00:18:06,300
Maybe you'll evolve into
something with wings.
也许你会进化出翅膀的

280
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:18,690
Good morning, gentlemen.
早上好 先生们

281
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:20,700
Good morning.
早上好

282
00:18:21,780 --> 00:18:25,400
Is there some new kind of
casual Friday I don't know about?
还有我不知道的星期五便装日?

283
00:18:25,410 --> 00:18:28,050
No, he lives here now.
不是 他住在这里了

284
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:29,200
Really? Why?
是不是哟? 为啥?

285
00:18:29,210 --> 00:18:32,410
Well, since he won't take the
bus and he's too evolved to drive,
既然他不能做公车
又进化过了人类驾驶的阶段

286
00:18:32,420 --> 00:18:34,500
he decided it would be easier
to just sleep in his office
他觉得等到我完成我的实验前

287
00:18:34,540 --> 00:18:38,310
and shower in the radiation lab
until I'm finished with my experiment.
办公室睡觉和在辐射实验室
洗澡会好熬些

288
00:18:39,170 --> 00:18:42,300
But you finished your
experiment a week ago.
但你一周前就完成了

289
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:47,470
Yep.
对

290
00:18:55,250 --> 00:18:56,990
********
天啦

291
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,870
********
又出现了

292
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:01,290
********
肯定是老鼠

293
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:03,860
********
老鼠不会烤面包

294
00:19:03,870 --> 00:19:07,020
********
更不会剥面包皮

295
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:18,810
You saw nothing!
当作啥也没看见!

